IEW OF ELECTRONIC MAIL SERVICE SYSTEMS PLANNING FOR THE U.S. POSTAL SERVICE.     POSTAL SERVICE STUDIES OF AN ELECTRONIC MAIL SERVICE SYSTEM AND OF ELECTRONICCOMPUTER-ORIGINATED MAIL ARE REVIEWED. AS A RESULT OF THE REVIEW IT ISCONCLUDED THAT THE POSTAL SERVICE SHOULD CONTINUE TO DEVELOP ELECTRONIC MAILSERVICES INSOFAR AS THEY ENHANCE PRESENT PHYSICAL DELIVERY OF MESSAGES.ELECTRONIC MAIL SERVICES SHOULD BE MANAGED BY AN INDEPENDENT UNIT WITHIN THEPOSTAL SERVICE, AND CONTINUED MARKET RESEARCH WILL BE NEEDED TO DETERMINECUSTOMER NEEDS. PLANNING FOR THE NEW SERVICES SHOULD BE DONE IN PARTNERSHIPWITH LABOUR REPRESENTATIVES, AND THE SECURITY OF ELECTRONIC MAIL AGAINSTINSPECTION AND DISCLOSURE MUST BE ASSURED